/*
DMA(dynamic memory allocation => giving size or memory during run time , ex: giving the size of the memory through user during run time.
SMA=giving the size or memory during complile time , ex: declare the size of array during writing the program. 

4 types=>in DMA
 malloc
 calloc
 realloc
 free

 malloc=>ptr = (datatype_ptr)malloc(sizeof(datatype))  = here all the values going to stored in the heap(is a huge container) , and then it will become garbage value
 
 calloc => ptr =(datatype)calloc(n,size(data)) => take random n numbers and value will become '0';

